    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-3636189">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-3636189">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,3636189)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-3636189">
																		You&#039;re just a voice, pal - you don&#039;t know a DAMN THING about racing!
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227397" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;" >A Random Day</a></span> <span class="odate time_1511158593 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Nov 2017 06:16</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3636189">
									

<p>Theme song is <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4ik3lXEU0-0">Control</a>, by <a href="http://www.anachronsounds.de/">VNV Nation</a>.</p>
<p>Extra-special thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3122708); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3122708&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1511727270" alt="The Great Hippo" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3122708)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3122708); return false;">The Great Hippo</a></span> for being the Rick Rubin to my Yeezus. Special thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1379080&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1511727270" alt="Randomini" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1379080)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;">Randomini</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2038009&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1511727270" alt="TyGently" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2038009)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;">TyGently</a></span>, and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/minmin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(560062); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=560062&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1511727270" alt="minmin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=560062)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/minmin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(560062); return false;">minmin</a></span> for helping me clean up the fiddly bits and make this as good as it could be. Many thanks to everyone else who read this.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Some thoughts on the characters:</p>
<ul>
<li>The Rookie is bisexual (though with a strong hetero leaning).</li>
<li>The Inside Man, on the other hand, is aroace. He's also a wickedly powerful psychic</li>
<li>In earlier drafts, the twins that the Rookie banged were nekos.</li>
</ul>
<p>Some thoughts on the scenario:</p>
<ul>
<li>I'd wanted to write an action tale taking place on a train for about a year leading up to this piece. There are a bunch of reasons why:
<ul>
<li>Trains offer three very distinct environments for action to occur in: the open space around the train, where ambushes can occur; the inside of the train, which lends itself to frantic, close-quarters battles; and the top of the train, which provides a vehicle for high-speed brawls with a variety of environmental hazards from tunnels to the wind.</li>
<li>These three environments, then, lend themselves quite nicely to plot progression: exposition and denouement outside the train, rising and falling action inside the train, and the climax on top of the train. They also provide fantastic setpieces for each section of plot that you can build a story around.</li>
<li>The train, by virtue of being a moving obstacle, automatically lends the plot a sense of urgency and speed. This was especially crucial for the story, since speed is at the crux of the -Velocity series.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Originally, the train belonged to Marshall, Carter, and Dark. This idea was quickly shot down because my muses questioned why they would even be shipping things through an inter dimensional pipeline.</li>
<li>Alexylva came into the forefront near immediately, as the vague, not-yet-codified Phitransimun Combine provided the perfect opportunity to contextualize the train and why it would need to be heisted at all.</li>
</ul>
<p>Some thoughts on the soundtrack:</p>
<ul>
<li>I always have music on while writing - oftentimes I will be inspired to write by music. As a result, what I write to has a huge impact on how I write, influencing everything from dialogue to pacing to style.</li>
<li>I first started hunting for a good track for Terminal Velocity in February. I didn't find what I was looking for until November.</li>
<li>I first envisioned the scenario of hijacking a train while listening to <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7T-iX41IFxc">Kunst</a> by <a href="https://kmfdm.net">KMFDM</a>. But then the 3000 contest happened and I completely lost track of the song.</li>
<li>In July I started drafting the tale and burned through most of <a href="https://runthejewels.com">Run the Jewels</a>' discography in the process, but was unsatisfied by the overuse of exposition.</li>
<li>I then tried writing to <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GwWGW8-x6OY">Satanic Rites</a> by <a href="https://perturbator.bandcamp.com">Perturbator</a>, but it didn't work, so I switched gears entirely to focus on <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/guns-pointed-hub">Guns Pointed at the Head of God</a>.</li>
<li>When fall rolled around, I got hooked on <a href="http://thirdworlds.net">Death Grips</a> and thought that <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fW3WzCx0ecw">Runway A</a> would be the track I needed. It wasn't (though it was fantastic for reading the final arcs of <em>Steel Ball Run</em>).</li>
<li>At the end of October, I re-watched the fantastic movie <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1483797/">Redline</a> and discovered a fantastic <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p9PR9TkHUTQ">AMV of the film for Control</a>. The sheer speed of Redline coupled with the smashing club beats of VNV Nation were exactly what I needed to energize my writing juices. I discarded the old draft that I had been piecemealing together since July and rewrote almost all of it from scratch within two weeks - which is what you just read.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;commentary</a></div>
</div>
</div>

